What you need to know:  On Thursday, Fifa president Gianni Infantino announced Kenya’s indefinite suspension from international football activities, citing government interferenceWhile terming the decision by Fifa to suspend Kenya as “harsh”, former FKF president Sam Nyamweya said the government and the world football governing body must now agree to a normalization committeeFKF presidential aspirants Twaha Mbarak and journalist Milton Nyakundi said the suspension gives Kenya time to put its house in order